cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.FL

The paper discusses a specification language for the verification of relational properties in software systems, which falls under the domain of software engineering (cs.SE). The language is table-based, which suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL). The focus on security properties such as confidentiality and integrity suggests a connection to cryptography (cs.CR). The use of regression testing and the verification of program equivalence suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses the applicability of the language to the domain of automated product systems, which suggests a connection to formal methods (cs.FL).
